рЯП° Introducing Organizations

We are introducing organizations as an entity to manage teams and projects effectively in Langfuse. This will likely have no
immediate impact on you (see below) but you, too, profit from our now much cleaner UI!
¬†
A bit of background: up until now, Langfuse's only organizing entity was the project. By grouping projects into organizations,
holistic role-based access control (RBAC) got much easier when managing many teams and projects in Langfuse.
¬†


рЯЩЕвАНвЩАпЄП No action required

You can continue to use your projects and API keys as usual.
You don't need to take any action as a result of this change. We have created a new organization for every project in your account
that retain your settings and permissions.
¬†
To learn more about organizations, head to our changelog [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-08-13-organizations].
¬†


рЯТѓ Take advantage of Organizations

You can now take advantage of streamlined permissions for users across projects:
¬†
 1. New Projects: Just create new projects within existing organizations, thereby grouping projects and applying default
    permissions across your team.

 1. Existing Projects: You can transfer existing projects you control into other organizations, thereby consolidating permissions
    and access.

¬†
For a detailed overview of roles and permissions in Langfuse, please see our documentation [https://langfuse.com/docs/rbac].
¬†
If you self-host Langfuse, organizations are available with versions >2.70.0
